== Content taken from [[User:Immanuelle/Yagi Shrine]] ==
{{ill|Yagi Shrine|ja|夜疑神社|simple|User:{{PAGENAME}}|en|Draft:Yagi Shrine}} (夜疑神社) is the shrine of the {{ill|Yagi clan|ja|八木氏|complete=true}}<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|title=夜疑神社|url=http://www.norichan.jp/jinja/benkyou2/yagi.htm|access-date=2023-12-13|website=www.norichan.jp}}</ref> it worships {{ill|Furutama-no-mikoto|ja|布留多摩命|6=simple|7=User:Immanuelle/Furutama|8=en|9=Draft:Furutama-no-mikoto}}.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|date=2016-08-18|title=��^�_�Ђ̌�Ր_|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160818202730/http://orange.zero.jp/hara.park/saijin.html|access-date=2024-03-23|website=web.archive.org}}</ref><ref name=":2" />

It has a [[Chinju no Mori]] around it.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2016-08-28|title=��^�_�Ђ̋����U��|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160828023607/http://orange.zero.jp/hara.park/sanpo.html|access-date=2024-03-23|website=web.archive.org}}</ref>

It is located at [[Kishiwada, Osaka]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=2016-08-18|title=��^�i�€�j�_��|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160818202710/http://orange.zero.jp/hara.park/index.html|access-date=2024-03-23|website=web.archive.org}}</ref> It is accessible from {{ill|Tadaoka Station|en}} on the {{ill|Nankai Main Line|en}}.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2016-08-28|title=��^�_�ЁE���ē�|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160828025755/http://orange.zero.jp/hara.park/mitiannai.html|access-date=2024-03-23|website=web.archive.org}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=夜疑神社【大阪府岸和田市】交通安全・厄除け祈願|url=https://www.yagi-jinja.jp/|access-date=2024-03-23|website=www.yagi-jinja.jp}}</ref>

There is a children's library on the shrine grounds.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2015-06-26|title=��^�_�Ђ̎�������|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150626222624/http://orange.zero.jp/hara.park/woody.html|access-date=2024-03-23|website=web.archive.org}}</ref>

== History ==
The year this shrine was founded is unknown, but it is also mentioned in [[Engishiki|the Engishiki]], which was created during [[Heian period|the Heian period]]<ref>{{Cite web|title=御由緒 {{!}} 夜疑神社【大阪府岸和田市】交通安全・厄除け祈願|url=https://www.yagi-jinja.jp/about/|access-date=2024-03-23|website=www.yagi-jinja.jp}}</ref>. In the {{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|en}} compiled in the early Heian period, there is a description indicates that the Yagi clan, an ancient powerful clan, enshrined their ancestral deity, {{ill|Furutama-no-mikoto|ja|布留多摩命|6=simple|7=User:Immanuelle/Furutama|8=en|9=Draft:Furutama-no-mikoto}}.  {{Sfn|岸和田市観光振興協会|1993}} . Several shrines were merged with it during the [[Meiji period]] <ref name=":0" />{{Sfn|岸和田市観光振興協会|1993}} . It was promoted to Go-sha in [[1943]]. {{Sfn|大阪府神道青年会|1971}}
