{{Expand Japanese}}
{{ill|Yagi clan|ja|八木氏|6=simple|7=User:Immanuelle/Yagi clan|8=en:draft|complete=true}} is a [[Japanese clans|Japanese clan]] descended from {{ill|Furutama-no-mikoto|ja|布留多摩命|simple|User:Immanuelle/Furutama}}. Their shrine is {{ill|Yagi Shrine|ja|夜疑神社|simple|User:Immanuelle/Yagi Shrine}}.<ref name="www.norichan.jp">{{Cite web|title=夜疑神社|url=http://www.norichan.jp/jinja/benkyou2/yagi.htm|access-date=2023-12-13|website=www.norichan.jp}}</ref> Where they worshipped their ancestral deity {{ill|Furutama-no-mikoto|ja|布留多摩命|6=simple|7=User:Immanuelle/Furutama|8=en:draft|9=Furutama-no-mikoto|10=fr|11=Furutama}}.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2016-08-18|title=��^�_�Ђ̌�Ր_|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160818202730/http://orange.zero.jp/hara.park/saijin.html|access-date=2024-03-23|website=web.archive.org}}</ref><ref name="www.norichan.jp" />
They owned {{ill|Wakasa Oniga Castle|en}}
== History == It is unknown when the {{ill|Yagi clan|ja|八木氏|6=simple|7=User:Immanuelle/Yagi clan|8=en:draft|complete=true}} built {{ill|Yagi Shrine|ja|夜疑神社|simple|User:Immanuelle/Yagi Shrine|en|Draft:Yagi Shrine}}, but it is also mentioned in the [[Engishiki|Engishiki]], which was created during the [[Heian period|Heian period]]<ref>{{Cite web|title=御由緒 {{!}} 夜疑神社【大阪府岸和田市】交通安全・厄除け祈願|url=https://www.yagi-jinja.jp/about/|access-date=2024-03-23|website=www.yagi-jinja.jp}}</ref>. In the {{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|en}} compiled in the early Heian period, there is a description indicates that the Yagi clan, an ancient powerful clan, enshrined their ancestral deity, {{ill|Furutama-no-mikoto|ja|布留多摩命|6=simple|7=User:Immanuelle/Furutama|8=en:draft|9=Furutama-no-mikoto|10=fr|11=Furutama}}. {{Sfn|岸和田市観光振興協会|1993}} .
{{Short description|Japanese Kamakura-period castle}}
The Yagi clan ruled {{Ill|Yagi Castle|en}} and the surrounding area for centuries. During the {{ill|Muromachi period|en}}, Tajima came under the control of the powerful {{ill|Yamana clan|en}}, and the Yagi accepted the Yamana as overlords. However, following the {{ill|Onin War|en}} the power of the Yamana was greatly weakened. In 1575, the 15th castellan of Yagi Castle, Yagi Toyonobu was approached by both the {{ill|Mōri clan|en}} from the west, and {{ill|Oda Nobunaga|en}} from the east. Initially, the Yagi cooperated with the Mōri, but in 1579 surrendered to Nobunaga's general, {{ill|Toyotomi Hidenaga|en}} in exchange for being allowed to keep their castle and territory. As per the terms of his surrender, Yagi Toyonobu was ordered to lead an army against the Mōri at {{ill|Tottori Castle|en}} in 1580 and was ordered togaed Wakasa Oni-ga-jo Castle (also in Tottori). He was defeated in a counterattack by Mori forces in 1581, and went missing-in-action. Consequently, {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|en}} seized Yagi Castle and awarded it to {{ill|Bessho Shigemune|ja|別所重宗}} as part of a 15,000 ''{{ill|koku|en}}'' fief.<ref name="Shiseki">{{cite book |last1=Isomura |first1=Yukio |last2=Sakai |first2=Hideya |title=(国指定史跡事典) National Historic Site Encyclopedia |date=2012 |publisher=学生社 |isbn=4311750404}} {{in lang|ja}}</ref> [[Category:dd]][[ja:八木氏]]<!-- Content taken from [[Yagi Castle]] -->
